				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">With the amount of content that currently exists in the game, I have to take the stance that it's GoD mobs that are the problem, not mages' lack of ability to deal with the issue.
<br />

<br />
Can we honestly claim that some other class is able to more easily deal with the wandering trash that shows up and quads for 1200?  The DS dispelling Calliav bugs me (I think that needs a fix), but otherwise its GoD that's the problem, not the mage class.  Trivializing the rest of the game is just... wrong.
<br />

<br />
The issue is that GoD has essentially trivialized the rest of the encounters in the game -- much moreso than even PoP did.  If players are buffed up to deal with that kind of power, the rest of the game becomes trivial indirectly.<br />_________________<br />Arhallia Ironborne
<br />
<span style="color: red">65th Arch Convoker</span>
<br />
Toenan Twosoks
<br />
<span style="color: green">56th Animist</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">Alliance of the Arcane</span></span>
