				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Again I disagree.  Level 60 is what trivialized the "old world", not Kunark gear.  Level 65 is what trivialized *some* of Luclin and Velious, and most of Kunark.
<br />

<br />
GoD did not come with Level 70.  Adding healing improvements of this magnitude will not make the difference from a raiding perspective.  They will only serve to further trivialize old content.  How much it trivializes the old content is my concern -- I'm fine with being able to sustain 50k hitpoints of pet versus some mob.  I'm saying 100k is too far, especially if its totally casual because buffed pets become hitpoint buffers beyond anything most PoP gods had to deal with, and can mitigate damage like an Ornate-armor equipped L60 warrior or better.
<br />

<br />
From my pov, its the raid and group xp/abilities and enchancements (group and raid hp/atk/mana increase, etc.)  that are meant to overcome to ridiculous power of GoD mobs.  We should be fighting for those abilities to enhance pets, if that was Sony's plan, and not trying to make our pets ridiculous hp buffers with corresponding CHs.<br />_________________<br />Arhallia Ironborne
