				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Naladini,
<br />

<br />
  I think the answer is:
<br />

<br />
1: Remove the recast time on Planar Renewal. 
<br />

<br />
2: Still need a new heal, no matter how you slice and dice it, pets will get hurt and healing them means a loss of DPS. A 2500 point heal for 300 mana works, cast time 6 seconds, 2.5 recast.
<br />

<br />
3: AA skill for improved healing as druids get, as they get SCS now.
<br />

<br />
4: Lay on hands for pets should be a Complete Heal as can only be used once every 9 minutes. If not a CH than at least 75% of the hit points, the way it is now, it helps a lot, but can be better as even Rytan suggested.
<br />

<br />
I think that would go a long ways to finishing up pet ballancing for mages. The amount of the proposed new heal may need to go up or down a bit decided upon after testing. The pets are upgraded now to the point they are viable in PoP (not tested yet in GoD zones), but still need to be healed as they can't solo the mobs, which makes sense. Just remove the recast delay on Planar Renewal, and a new heal spell, and we have options to heal it or nuke it as the fight goes on. 
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
