			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since the word isn't in on where the pet mitigation/avoidance truly lies yet, I'm holding off a bit, rather than derail this with ill-conceived numbers that should just be ignored anyways.
<br />

<br />
The issues are the same, no matter the level of improvements:
<br />

<br />
* Quick heal for unexpected damage -- 2146 from Mend Companion is completely insufficient, though the method and refresh time are reasonable (compare to DivArb use on PCs).
<br />

<br />
* Ability to trade damage casting for healing -- Planar Renewal, against the mobs in PoP and especially GoD is too slow on cycle time, and too weak on HPs healed. Useful for healing when AoEs or other damage weaken a pet and the PC healers are attending to the PCs (as they probably should). Useful for "Oh ^%$#!" situations. Cast time must be drastically reduced as the current rate of damage done to pets does not allow for long cast-time spells. HP/sec also needs some (yet-to-be-determined) boost, based on the DPS being taken by the pet in grouping/raiding situations.
<br />

<br />
I'm unable to comment in much more depth without hard numbers.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
